reviewText:
Awesome...the best one in the entire series!
In the final chapter of the Five Nights at Freddy's quadrilogy, you play as a child in his bedroom. But this time you don't have security cameras or a maintenance panel to keep you safe. You only have a flashlight and most importantly your common sense. Why? Because to survive you have to listen carefully for breathing before flashing the halls, and refusing to do so will cause the monsters to attack, which is never a good thing!

PROS:
+Absolutely terrifying;
+Simple but effective mechanics;
+Very good atmosphere;
+Good replayability (thanks to the challenges introduced in the Halloween update).

CONS:
-It gets repetitive pretty fast;
-Story is very confusing (a bad thing considering it's the final chapter of the series).

It's not a perfect game surely, but if you want an arcade horror game I recommend you to grab it (in sale possibly). If you're a fan of the series like me, just get it. You won't regret.

Oh look, The 4th game has come out. That was quick. Uh..well this game is spooky and that's all there is to it. Currently I can't even get past Night 3 because I can't hear da breathing ;-;

I would say it's best one in the series, bringing back up the spooks from FNAF 1 and then putting it in FNAF 4 but with even more spooks.


So ya. Bye.
